  "authors": [],
  "body": {
    "comment": "I vote YES on \"Withdraw 120M ADA for AlphaGrowth's Cardano PRIME\" as a conscious exception. Normally I would first fund a smaller research and planning phase, let the team\nshow the results, and then let DReps vote separately on the large spending phase. Here I accept that the full 120M ADA is approved now, although an Operating Group can later\ndecide whether roughly 90M goes to Phase 3; that group is an extra checkpoint, not a second DRep vote. I vote YES because Cardano needs a serious attempt to improve\nliquidity and adoption, and AlphaGrowth, Intersect, the phase checkpoint and return of unused funds make this a credible but risky attempt rather than a blank cheque. I\nexpect clear public reporting on where the money goes, who benefits, what results last after incentives end, and when money must stop or return to the Treasury."
  },
  "hashAlgorithm": "blake2b-256"
}